{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"1V9tDyQwkgBuhWMngZc6p","title":"Limit Theorems","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"central-limit-theorem":{"type":"header","text":"Central Limit Theorem","value":"central-limit-theorem","line":8,"column":0},"law-of-large-numbers":{"type":"header","text":"Law of Large Numbers","value":"law-of-large-numbers","line":10,"column":0},"slutskycontinuous-mapping-theorem":{"type":"header","text":"Slutsky/Continuous Mapping Theorem","value":"slutskycontinuous-mapping-theorem","line":18,"column":0},"cramer-wold-device":{"type":"header","text":"Cramer-Wold Device","value":"cramer-wold-device","line":30,"column":0},"":{"type":"header","text":"","value":"","line":32,"column":0}},"fname":"Appendix.Limit_theorems","updated":1636418351270,"created":1636344103536,"parent":"CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"a42bdcc20380e88baadc5364d99805ef","custom":{}},"body":"<h2 id=\"central-limit-theorem\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#central-limit-theorem\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Central Limit Theorem</h2>\n<h2 id=\"law-of-large-numbers\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#law-of-large-numbers\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Law of Large Numbers</h2>\n<p>There are different sets of sufficient conditions for the WLLN.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Kolmogorov, all X are i.i.d. with finite expectation. Note that this implies the SLLN.</li>\n<li>Chebyshev, all X are uncorrelated, such that the variance is finite, and the sample variance converges to 0 asymptotically</li>\n<li>All X have finite variance, and sample variance converges to 0 asymptotically. Additionally, all sample covariances, and the sum of all sample covariances are finite (looser version of the Chebyshev version).</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"slutskycontinuous-mapping-theorem\"><a